<DIV2 TYPE="part">
<HEAD>The <HI>Te&s;timony</HI> of the <HI>Holy Scriptures</HI> concerning the <HI>LAW, SPIRIT, WORD, GRACE, LOVE</HI> and <HI>POWER</HI> of <HI>GOD</HI> within.</HEAD>
<LIST>
<ITEM><LABEL><HI>P&s;alm</HI> xxxvii. 31.</LABEL> THE law of his God is in his heart, none of his &s;teps &s;hall &s;lide.</ITEM>
<ITEM><LABEL><HI>P&s;alm</HI> xl. 8.</LABEL> I delight to do thy will, O my God: Yea, thy law is within my heart.</ITEM>
<ITEM><LABEL><HI>I&s;a.</HI> li. 7.</LABEL> Hearken unto me, ye that know righteou&s;ne&s;s, the people in who&s;e heart is my law; fear ye not the reproach of men, neither be ye afraid of their reviling.</ITEM>
<ITEM><LABEL><HI>Rom.</HI> ii. 14.</LABEL> For when the <HI>Gentiles</HI> which have not the law, do by nature the things contained in the law, the&s;e having not the law, are a law unto them&s;elves.</ITEM>
